1031
00:51:16,011 --> 00:51:17,221
[grunts]

1032
00:51:25,103 --> 00:51:27,689
[groaning in pain]

1033
00:51:27,773 --> 00:51:29,066
[Mother's Milk] Goddamn.

1034
00:51:29,149 --> 00:51:31,652
I only seen shit like this one other time.

1035
00:51:33,320 --> 00:51:37,783
It was on you outside of that truck stop
whore house on I-23. [laughs]

1036
00:51:37,866 --> 00:51:40,911
[Butcher] Soldier Cunt down.
Homelander to go.

1037
00:51:40,994 --> 00:51:43,580
-We fucking did it.
-About time.

1038
00:51:44,581 --> 00:51:46,375
[door opens]

1039
00:51:47,835 --> 00:51:48,919
Mon coeur.

1040
00:51:50,128 --> 00:51:52,589
[gentle music playing]

1041
00:51:56,635 --> 00:51:58,345
Let's run away.

1042
00:52:00,264 --> 00:52:01,265
What?

1043
00:52:01,348 --> 00:52:05,727
There are over 50 uninhabited islands
in the Pacific.

1044
00:52:05,811 --> 00:52:10,774
We just need to find one so remote,
nobody will ever find us.

1045
00:52:12,818 --> 00:52:14,695
You were right.

1046
00:52:14,778 --> 00:52:19,324
This virus,
there is no containing it, no stopping it.

1047
00:52:19,408 --> 00:52:22,077
I do not know how to protect you from it,

1048
00:52:22,160 --> 00:52:26,665
except to take you as far away
from here as possible.

1049
00:52:36,091 --> 00:52:40,262
We have to stay.

1050
00:52:42,139 --> 00:52:46,310
Mon amour,
you did not see its carnage.

1051
00:52:46,393 --> 00:52:48,896
-It's too dangerous.
-It's dangerous for everyone now.

1052
00:52:48,979 --> 00:52:51,023
Innocent people are being round up.

1053
00:52:51,106 --> 00:52:53,775
No.
Je peux pas.

1054
00:52:53,859 --> 00:52:56,445
Don't ask me to watch you die.

1055
00:52:56,528 --> 00:52:58,864
I think this is how we make amends.

1056
00:53:00,449 --> 00:53:02,868
For the lives we've taken.
I think we have to...

1057
00:53:04,286 --> 00:53:06,622
Get up every day and keep going?

1058
00:53:06,705 --> 00:53:08,457
[somber music playing]

1059
00:53:12,002 --> 00:53:13,128
Oui.

1060
00:53:18,133 --> 00:53:19,509
C'est ça.

1061
00:53:22,137 --> 00:53:23,847
[vape hissing]

1062
00:53:35,776 --> 00:53:37,486
You're allowed to freak out, you know.

1063
00:53:37,569 --> 00:53:39,237
This virus.

1064
00:53:41,073 --> 00:53:42,574
It's fucking brutal.

1065
00:53:42,658 --> 00:53:46,870
I don't know, for Rock Hard,
I'd say it's an improvement.

1066
00:53:49,665 --> 00:53:52,250
I haven't exactly had
a magical year either.

1067
00:53:52,334 --> 00:53:54,169
Neither of us is fine.

1068
00:53:55,837 --> 00:53:57,589
And we shouldn't be.

1069
00:53:57,673 --> 00:53:59,633
And if you don't want to talk about it,

1070
00:53:59,716 --> 00:54:01,593
-you don't have to.
-Perfect.

1071
00:54:01,677 --> 00:54:03,637
But I'm not letting you die.

1072
00:54:06,515 --> 00:54:08,141
I'm gonna keep fighting.

1073
00:54:10,852 --> 00:54:14,564
And if you can't,
then I'm just gonna fight for both of us.

1074
00:54:16,358 --> 00:54:20,112
But just don't turn into
fucking Butcher, okay?

1075
00:54:20,195 --> 00:54:22,197
[slow, dramatic music playing]

1076
00:54:31,331 --> 00:54:32,457
[door opens]

1077
00:54:36,378 --> 00:54:39,631
I know. I'm late.

1078
00:54:43,135 --> 00:54:45,137
[Terror whining softly]

1079
00:54:53,645 --> 00:54:55,397
All right, Terror.

1080
00:54:57,816 --> 00:55:00,068
Time for your meds.

1081
00:55:03,864 --> 00:55:05,365
Oh, yeah.

1082
00:55:08,118 --> 00:55:10,996
-Who's a good boy, ay?
-[whines softly]

1083
00:55:17,127 --> 00:55:19,463
[spraying]

1084
00:55:22,007 --> 00:55:23,508
[booming thud]

1085
00:55:24,760 --> 00:55:25,761
Whoa, hey.

1086
00:55:25,844 --> 00:55:27,095
Be careful, sir.

1087
00:55:27,179 --> 00:55:28,346
There's a viral contagion.

1088
00:55:28,430 --> 00:55:31,683
I got here as soon as I heard,
and I locked shit down.

1089
00:55:31,767 --> 00:55:35,520
Sending Soldier Boy to test the waters,
pretty fucking strategic, sir.

1090
00:55:35,604 --> 00:55:38,690
You're always playing 3D chess,
aren't you?

1091
00:55:38,774 --> 00:55:40,525
I told him to report back.

1092
00:55:40,609 --> 00:55:43,904
Told him not to go in alone.
Why would he do that?

1093
00:55:43,987 --> 00:55:46,323
Well, it's more like Soldier Doy,

1094
00:55:46,406 --> 00:55:48,033
-am I right?
-Leave.

1095
00:55:49,159 --> 00:55:50,577
Well, I just, um, got to be here, sir.

1096
00:55:50,660 --> 00:55:52,245
-To do the--
-Should've been you.

1097
00:55:52,329 --> 00:55:53,371
Okay.

1098
00:55:53,455 --> 00:55:55,457
-I'm sorry.
-Leave.

1099
00:55:55,540 --> 00:55:57,542
[tense music playing]

1100
00:56:01,463 --> 00:56:03,381
I was swimming.

1101
00:56:09,387 --> 00:56:10,722
[inhales sharply]

1102
00:56:12,808 --> 00:56:14,434
[somber music playing]

1103
00:56:20,690 --> 00:56:22,150
No...

1104
00:56:24,736 --> 00:56:26,446
No...

1105
00:56:27,989 --> 00:56:30,033
Not you, too.

1106
00:56:30,117 --> 00:56:32,285
Not you.

1107
00:56:35,247 --> 00:56:36,540
[grunting]

1108
00:56:40,001 --> 00:56:42,504
Why does everyone keep leaving me?

1109
00:56:45,340 --> 00:56:48,301
I'm sorry. [sniffles]

